The Taraba State kidnap kingpin, Hamisu Bala, popularly known as Wadume, has been re-arrested. He has been taken to the Louis Edet House, Force headquarters in Abuja, The Nation reports. Wadume escaped after soldiers attacked and killed policemen who had captured him. The incident occurred along Ibi-Wukari road in Taraba State on August 6. Nigeria’s Chief of Defence Staff, Gen Abayomi Gabriel Olonisakin had constituted a 7 man Joint Investigation Panel to probe the incident. Details later… Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.